    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul General at Peiping (
                        Clubb
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1330</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1330</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-03-20T00:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1330">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.7146/3–2049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-20T13:00:00+08:00">March 20, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 20.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>444. ReContel 441, March 19.<note n="44" xml:id="d1330fn44">Not printed.</note>
                    Representative Military Control Commission last evening called consular compound
                    and questioned gateman re various matters pertaining to Consulate including
                    radio. In accord standing instructions, gateman replied uninformed, suggested
                    officer should visit during office hours. Latter stated he would return 0900
                    Monday.</p>
                <pb facs="1082" n="1072" xml:id="pg_1072"/>
                <p>British Consular [<hi rend="italic">Consul</hi>] reports still no visit this [<hi rend="italic">his</hi>] office.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Nanking and Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
